<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Let me know what you think...also if there are any weak points to this strategy.<br>
My idea was to form an ENTIRE group of magicians. I'm not sure if anyone's ever tried this, or if it would even work...<br>
So here's how it might work:<p>

1. 6 magicians group together<br>
2. each of them summon pets, a variety would probably work best. Maybe 3 earth and one of each of the others?<br>
3. Everyone casts burnout on the pets(pet buff for AC, att, and def). <br>
4. Everyone has renew elements memmed. (who needs a cleric when the only tanks are pets, and you can heal them?)<br>
5. Every pet gets a fire shield too.<p>

Now you've got a group of essentialy 12 members. Another huge advantage I think is the fact that all the tanks are totally expendable. If one dies, the mage who's pet it was can just summon another while the other 5 pets keep fighting. Also, pets taunt REALLY well. I think with this strategy you could be very effective in an open area, or in an area suitable for pulling (unrest, ect). The other nifty thing is you've got 6 magicians backing up the pets with DD. That's a hell of alot of firepower. <p>

In my opinion this would be worth trying if only for the excellent roleplay value. Can you imagine the battle scenes? Talk about an amazing sight! I'm on Morrel-Thule and if any other magicians around my level would be interested in trying this let me know. Those of you reading this who play on other servers, at least let me know if you think this would or would not work and why. I'd really appreciate some feedback!<p>

Thanks in advance,<p>

Gobo<br>
Apprentice Magician of the 12th circle<br>
Ak'anon, Norrath<br>
(Morell-Thule)</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
